result.execSummary:
The defendant Luis Serna was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: THE DEPARTMENT OF CORRECTIONS SHALL DEDUCT RESTITUTION AND ALL OTHER COURT OBLIGATIONS AT THE RATE OF 25% OF ALL MONIES RECEIVED WHILE INCARCERATED.

superMiscConds.notes:
Pay court costs and Department of Corrections Supervision fees. If the defendant is discharged from Extended Supervision with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment may be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.
-------------------------

No contact with victim A.S. without victim's consent. Court recognizes that Ms. Serna stated a desire to have the kids visit with Mr. Serna and the Court is not opposed to this.
-------------------------

Sex offender assessment and treatment. Any other treatment deemed necessary. Register and comply with Sex Offender Registration.   Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, and pay DNA analysis surcharge.
-------------------------
